properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 1 at 5:29AM PST until February 1 at 10:28PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Skokomish River At Potlatch affecting Mason County
Bogachiel River Near La Push affecting Clallam County

Olympic Peninsula Region

The second round of heavy rain has moved into the Olympics early
this morning with one to two inches reported in the last six hours
ending at 5 am. The heavy rain will move south through the area
later this morning.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Bogachiel River Near La Push
* Until this evening.
* At  4:30 AM Saturday the stage was 38.6 feet.
* Flood stage is 37.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is occurring and Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will continue to rise and crest near 38.8 feet
around 7 AM Saturday. The river will fall below flood stage early
this afternoon.
* Impact...At 37.0 feet, the Bogachiel River will cause flooding of
State Highway 110 near the Bogachiel bridge...closing the road.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
